    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### **Business Interpretation**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ufZzwkKGALkc"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Recent repayment behavior is the strongest signal\n",
        "\n",
        "Historical bill amounts matter less than payment delays\n",
        "\n",
        "Demographics have weaker predictive power"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Sm0cggobXt0D"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**🔥 STEP 3: Feature Engineering & Preprocessing (Advanced)**\n",
        "\n",
        "This step is where you actively improve model performance.\n",
        "Many people skip this — don’t.\n",
        "\n",
        "🎯 Objective\n",
        "\n",
        "Clean bad categories\n",
        "\n",
        "Engineer meaningful features\n",
        "\n",
        "Prepare data for ML models\n",
        "\n",
        "Avoid data leakage\n",
        "\n",
        "🧹 Step 3.1: Fix Invalid Categorical Values\n",
        "EDUCATION\n",
        "\n",
        "Original values:\n",
        "\n",
        "1,2,3,4 → valid\n",
        "\n",
        "0,5,6 → invalid\n",
        "\n",
        "👉 Group invalid ones as 4 = “Others”"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sv2liEVSfxfM"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df['EDUCATION'] = df['EDUCATION'].replace([0,5,6], 4)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wIluDIZyXwUk"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "MARRIAGE\n",
        "\n",
        "1,2 → valid\n",
        "\n",
        "0 → invalid"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "G9e0nZ7jf43C"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df['MARRIAGE'] = df['MARRIAGE'].replace(0, 3)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PKmv8JpFf6QY"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### 🧠 **Understand PAY_X Values**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "r-oduLQHAv3E"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "PAY_X values:\n",
        "\n",
        "-2 → No consumption\n",
        "\n",
        "-1 → Paid duly\n",
        "\n",
        "0 → Revolving credit\n",
        "\n",
        "1,2,3... → Delay in months\n",
        "\n",
        "👉 Transform into binary delayed / not delayed"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "g7U--yvfgLVA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "pay_cols = ['PAY_0','PAY_2','PAY_3','PAY_4','PAY_5','PAY_6']\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in pay_cols:\n",
        "    df[col + '_DELAY'] = (df[col] > 0).astype(int)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "84TLS8vegM75"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**📐 Step 3.3: Feature Engineering (Advanced)**\n",
        "Total bill & payment behavior"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Nt_0eSdCgWdX"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "bill_cols = ['BILL_AMT1','BILL_AMT2','BILL_AMT3','BILL_AMT4','BILL_AMT5','BILL_AMT6']\n",
        "pay_amt_cols = ['PAY_AMT1','PAY_AMT2','PAY_AMT3','PAY_AMT4','PAY_AMT5','PAY_AMT6']\n",
        "\n",
        "df['TOTAL_BILL'] = df[bill_cols].sum(axis=1)\n",
        "df['TOTAL_PAY'] = df[pay_amt_cols].sum(axis=1)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NC2NOCirgWHh"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Payment ratio (VERY POWERFUL FEATURE)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PqO3ccvIggdD"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Adding 1 to denominator to avoid divide by zero issue\n",
        "df['PAYMENT_RATIO'] = df['TOTAL_PAY'] / (df['TOTAL_BILL'] + 1)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "364HdU0egiDY"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "🧪 Step 3.4: Train–Test Split (Correct Way)\n",
        "\n",
        "⚠️ Always stratify for imbalanced data."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YMY3UmTqgl9A"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "\n",
        "X = df.drop(columns=['default'])\n",
        "y = df['default']\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "23V3OQs8gqQX"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "⚖️ Step 3.5: Scaling (Important!)\n",
        "\n",
        "Tree models don’t need scaling\n",
        "Linear models DO."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d4uhobYEgzA6"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
        "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jUSvwtjWg0hX"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "🚀 STEP 4: Model Building (Baseline → Advanced)\n",
        "\n",
        "We’ll do this like a senior data scientist: simple → strong → business-aware.\n",
        "\n",
        "🎯 Objective\n",
        "\n",
        "Build baseline model\n",
        "\n",
        "Handle class imbalance properly\n",
        "\n",
        "Compare multiple algorithms\n",
        "\n",
        "Evaluate with correct metrics"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n1bnqf07hK0C"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "4️⃣.1 Baseline Model: Logistic Regression\n",
        "Why start here?\n",
        "\n",
        "Interpretable\n",
        "\n",
        "Fast\n",
        "\n",
        "Sets a performance benchmark"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WjJHGOTohNSl"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_auc_score\n",
        "\n",
        "# Class weight balanced to handle imbalance , max_iteration to 1000 to converge fully\n",
        "lr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, class_weight='balanced')\n",
        "#Train model\n",
        "lr.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_pred = lr.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
        "#“Give me probability of Class 1 default only will use for AUC ROC”\n",
        "y_proba = lr.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:,1]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "print(\"ROC-AUC:\", roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba))\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "nM_aCBIxhO2X",
        "outputId": "af596b97-1d82-473b-9a70-a30cc18959c4"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "              precision    recall  f1-score   support\n",
            "\n",
            "           0       0.87      0.83      0.85      4673\n",
            "           1       0.48      0.56      0.51      1327\n",
            "\n",
            "    accuracy                           0.77      6000\n",
            "   macro avg       0.67      0.69      0.68      6000\n",
            "weighted avg       0.78      0.77      0.77      6000\n",
            "\n",
            "ROC-AUC: 0.7447798936667553\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### 🎯 What Precision & Recall REALLY mean here\n",
        "\n",
        "We care MOST about class 1 (default).\n",
        "\n",
        "**🔴 Precision = 0.48 (for class 1)**\n",
        "Meaning:\n",
        "\n",
        "Out of all customers the model predicted as defaulters,\n",
        "only 48% actually defaulted.\n",
        "\n",
        "In simple words:\n",
        "\n",
        "Model raises many alarms\n",
        "\n",
        "About half of them are false alarms\n",
        "\n",
        "**📌 Business meaning:**\n",
        "\n",
        "Some good customers may be flagged as risky\n",
        "\n",
        "That’s acceptable if the goal is risk control\n",
        "\n",
        "🟢 Recall = 0.56 (for class 1) ⭐ MORE IMPORTANT\n",
        "Meaning:\n",
        "\n",
        "Out of all real defaulters,\n",
        "the model correctly catches 56% of them\n",
        "\n",
        "In simple words:\n",
        "\n",
        "The model finds more than half of risky customers\n",
        "\n",
        "But still misses 44% of defaulters\n",
        "\n",
        "**📌 Business meaning:**\n",
        "\n",
        "Better than random\n",
        "\n",
        "But still losing money from missed defaulters"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PcO6YSAkJN0c"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**max_iter=1000**\n",
        "\n",
        "Logistic regression learns step by step\n",
        "\n",
        "Sometimes it needs more steps to finish\n",
        "\n",
        "1000 ensures it converges properly\n",
        "\n",
        "**class_weight='balanced' ⭐ VERY IMPORTANT**\n",
        "\n",
        "Our data has:\n",
        "\n",
        "Many 0 (non-default)\n",
        "\n",
        "Few 1 (default)\n",
        "\n",
        "This tells the model:\n",
        "\n",
        "“Mistakes on defaulters are MORE serious.”\n",
        "\n",
        "So:\n",
        "\n",
        "Default class gets higher weight\n",
        "\n",
        "Model pays more attention to risky customers\n",
        "\n",
        "**📌 Interview line:**\n",
        "\n",
        "“I used class-weighted logistic regression to handle class imbalance.”\n",
        "\n",
        "**y_pred = lr.predict(X_test_scaled)**\n",
        "\n",
        "Model looks at new, unseen data\n",
        "\n",
        "**Predicts:**\n",
        "\n",
        "0 → will not default\n",
        "\n",
        "1 → will default\n",
        "\n",
        "⚠️ Uses default threshold = 0.5\n",
        "\n",
        "**y_proba = lr.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:,1]**\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Meaning:\n",
        "\n",
        "Column 0 → probability of class 0\n",
        "\n",
        "Column 1 → probability of class 1 (default)\n",
        "\n",
        "[:,1] means:\n",
        "\n",
        "“Give me probability of default only will use for AUC ROC”"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rU5IcMaIEUY_"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "👉 Key insight to note:\n",
        "\n",
        "Accuracy may look decent\n",
        "\n",
        "Recall for default class improves due to class_weight='balanced'"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nMLCCOa1hclz"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "4️⃣.2 Why class_weight='balanced'?\n",
        "\n",
        "Because:\n",
        "\n",
        "Dataset is imbalanced\n",
        "\n",
        "Penalizes misclassification of minority class more\n",
        "\n",
        "Alternative to SMOTE (less leakage risk)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7a2fnbnOhgyA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "📌 Interview line:\n",
        "\n",
        "“I prefer class-weighted models over oversampling initially to avoid synthetic noise.”"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "t7cFQnCBhpDe"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### 4️⃣.3 Tree-Based Model: Random Forest"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5ndsBD7phrK1"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
        "\n",
        "# 200 decision trees used , random_state to get same result everytime we run code\n",
        "rf = RandomForestClassifier(\n",
        "    n_estimators=200,\n",
        "    class_weight='balanced',\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# No need to scale since it is decision tree\n",
        "rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_proba_rf = rf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\n",
        "print(\"ROC-AUC (RF):\", roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba_rf))\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "W343BhCwhcXr",
        "outputId": "24aa997a-d581-4c03-a6dd-ee8b84bbf460"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "ROC-AUC (RF): 0.7607249618654583\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "👉 Expect:\n",
        "\n",
        "Better non-linearity capture\n",
        "\n",
        "Less need for scaling"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UUcLLxhbh0Kv"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### 4️⃣.4 Advanced Model: XGBoost / LightGBM"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ch08A2njh5vQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from xgboost import XGBClassifier\n",
        "#scale_pos_weight: To handle class imbalance “Mistakes on class 1 are more expensive — pay more attention to it.”\n",
        "xgb = XGBClassifier(\n",
        "    scale_pos_weight = (y_train == 0).sum() / (y_train == 1).sum(),\n",
        "    eval_metric='logloss',\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "xgb.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_proba_xgb = xgb.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]\n",
        "print(\"ROC-AUC (XGB):\", roc_auc_score(y_test, y_proba_xgb))\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "A_k6bXb-h4cC",
        "outputId": "2fd21a41-3d51-400d-cb02-735910329b59"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "ROC-AUC (XGB): 0.756587853936844\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**eval_metric='logloss',**\n",
        "\n",
        "👉 Tells XGBoost how to measure error during training.\n",
        "\n",
        "logloss = penalizes confident wrong predictions heavily\n",
        "\n",
        "Works well for probability-based models\n",
        "\n",
        "Common choice for binary classification"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uHgAxMs9SeAX"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**📊 4️⃣.5 Metric Comparison (CRITICAL)**\n",
        "\n",
        "You should compare:\n",
        "\n",
        "Recall (Default = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "Precision\n",
        "\n",
        "ROC-AUC\n",
        "\n",
        "PR-AUC (next step)\n",
        "\n",
        "Accuracy ❌ (don’t trust it)\n",
        "\n",
        "🧠 What You Should Observe\n",
        "\n",
        "Logistic Regression → interpretable, stable\n",
        "\n",
        "Random Forest → captures interactions\n",
        "\n",
        "XGBoost → usually best ROC-AUC\n",
        "\n",
        "But…\n",
        "\n",
        "Best ROC-AUC ≠ best business model"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cH4jVr0qiMTE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**🚨 STEP 5: Threshold Tuning, PR-AUC & Business Impact**\n",
        "\n",
        "Most people stop at ROC-AUC.\n",
        "Senior data scientists do not.\n",
        "\n",
        "🎯 Objective\n",
        "\n",
        "Show why default threshold (0.5) is wrong\n",
        "\n",
        "Optimize for business goals\n",
        "\n",
        "Use Precision–Recall tradeoff\n",
        "\n",
        "Quantify financial impact\n",
        "\n",
        "❌ Why 0.5 Threshold Is Wrong\n",
        "\n",
        "In imbalanced problems:\n",
        "\n",
        "Positive class is rare\n",
        "\n",
        "Model rarely outputs probabilities > 0.5\n",
        "\n",
        "You miss many defaulters → huge loss\n",
        "\n",
        "📌 Interview line:\n",
        "\n",
        "“Probability calibration and threshold tuning are more important than model choice.”"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Xt2walk7iUgp"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**📈 STEP 5.1: Precision–Recall Curve**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PhsvN2PqiZ5B"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, average_precision_score\n",
        "\n",
        "precision, recall, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_proba_xgb)\n",
        "\n",
        "pr_auc = average_precision_score(y_test, y_proba_xgb)\n",
        "print(\"PR-AUC:\", pr_auc)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "FWo4VHMxhzIV",
        "outputId": "9b2cc14a-27f0-411b-a3bf-aab91dbe9496"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "PR-AUC: 0.5339968717792284\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "👉 PR-AUC is far more meaningful than ROC-AUC here.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "egnPM3cFig04"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**🎯 STEP 5.2: Find Optimal Threshold**\n",
        "\n",
        "Example: maximize F1-score"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QymqsUr7iivJ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "f1_scores = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall + 1e-6)\n",
        "best_threshold = thresholds[f1_scores[:-1].argmax()]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Best Threshold:\", best_threshold)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "IfN0VNXwilNw",
        "outputId": "c7af9723-5e59-4eb8-c7ae-72a57b4b2667"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Best Threshold: 0.53409785\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**🔄 STEP 5.3: Apply New Threshold**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vgQjf0ZcipQ9"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "y_pred_tuned = (y_proba_xgb >= best_threshold).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n",
        "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_tuned))\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "i_aZMOZriraj",
        "outputId": "d7000b39-d241-4d06-99e2-e50315e43411"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "              precision    recall  f1-score   support\n",
            "\n",
            "           0       0.87      0.84      0.85      4673\n",
            "           1       0.49      0.54      0.51      1327\n",
            "\n",
            "    accuracy                           0.78      6000\n",
            "   macro avg       0.68      0.69      0.68      6000\n",
            "weighted avg       0.78      0.78      0.78      6000\n",
            "\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "👉 Expected result:\n",
        "\n",
        "Recall ↑ significantly\n",
        "\n",
        "Precision ↓ slightly\n",
        "\n",
        "Overall business win"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WELlIKmhit-p"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**💰 STEP 5.4: Business Impact Simulation (Advanced)**\n",
        "\n",
        "Assume:\n",
        "\n",
        "Avg loss per default = ₹50,000\n",
        "\n",
        "Model catches more defaulters"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mi6oqs6giv6j"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "false_negatives = np.sum((y_test == 1) & (y_pred_tuned == 0))\n",
        "estimated_loss = false_negatives * 50000\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Estimated Loss (₹):\", estimated_loss)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
